3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey'd%20be%20exposed%20to%20high%20levels%20of%20solar%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-energy-radiation-hotspot-space-puzzles-astronomers-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosmic%20radiation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20harmful%20effects%20of%20zero-gravity%2C%20and%20a%20long%20period%20of%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpace%20radiation%20is%20arguably%20the%20biggest%20threat.%20Astronauts%20who%20spend%20just%20six%20months%20in%20space%20are%20exposed%20to%20roughly%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20radiation%20as%201%2C000%20chest%20X-rays%2C%20and%20this%20puts%20them%20at%20risk%20for%20cancer%2C%20nervous%20system%20damage%2C%20bone%20loss%2C%20and%20heart%20disease%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-transfer-spinoffs%2Fnasa-funded-space-radiation-research-fights-cancer-on-earth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20reduce%20radiation%20exposure%20and%20other%20harmful%20health%20effects%20is%20to%20shorten%20the%20length%20of%20the%20trip%2C%20Troy%20Howe%2C%20president%20of%20Howe%20Industries%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20That's%20why%20he's%20teamed%20up%20with%20NASA%20to%20develop%20the%20Pulsed%20Plasma%20Rocket%20(PPR)%3A%20a%20new%20rocket%20system%20that%20could%20shorten%20a%20round-trip%20to%20Mars%20to%20just%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20technology%20%26quot%3Bholds%20the%20potential%20to%20revolutionize%20space%20exploration%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fdirectorates%2Fstmd%2Fniac%2Fniac-studies%2Fpulsed-plasma-rocket-ppr-shielded-fast-transits-for-humans-to-mars%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20could%20one%20day%20take%20humans%20even%20further%20than%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2218475c81-b726-408b-9110-d9b28cd633bf%5C%22%3EHow%20a%20rocket%20could%20get%20us%20to%20Mars%20and%20back%20in%202%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222310%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20the%20Pulsed%20Plasma%20Rocket%20coasting%20through%20space%20with%20Earth%20in%20the%20distance%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6690321d8893442a5155e002%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221297%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIt%20will%20be%20another%2020%20years%20before%20the%20PPR%20is%20ready%20to%20blast%20into%20space.%20But%20when%20it%20is%2C%20Howe%20Industries%20hopes%20it'll%20significantly%20expand%20the%20range%20of%20human%20space%20exploration.%3Cp%3EHowe%20Industries%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PPR%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-astronauts-speak-out-boeing-starliner-spaceship-issues-space-station-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epropulsion%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20uses%20pulses%20of%20superheated%20plasma%20to%20generate%20a%20lot%20of%20thrust%20very%20efficiently.%20It's%20currently%20in%20phase%20two%20of%20development%2C%20funded%20by%20the%20NASA%20Innovative%20Advanced%20Concepts%20(NIAC)%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20phase%20two%20study%20is%20scheduled%20to%20begin%20this%20month%2C%20and%20is%20focused%20on%20optimizing%20the%20engine%20design%2C%20performing%20proof-of-concept%20experiments%2C%20and%20designing%20a%20PPR-powered%2C%20shielded%20spaceship%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-elevator-pros-cons-japan-design-revolutionize-space-travel-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20missions%20to%20Mars%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20advantage%20of%20the%20PPR%20is%20that%20it%20can%20make%20a%20spacecraft%20go%20really%2C%20really%20fast.%20It%20has%20both%20a%20high%20thrust%20and%20high%20specific%20impulse.%20Specific%20impulse%20is%20how%20quickly%20a%20rocket%20engine%20generates%20thrust%2C%20and%20thrust%20is%20the%20force%20that%20moves%20the%20spacecraft%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20PPR%20generates%2010%2C000%20newtons%20of%20thrust%20at%20a%20specific%20impulse%20of%205%2C000%20seconds.%20That%20means%20a%20PPR-equipped%20spacecraft%20carrying%20four%20to%20six%20passengers%20could%20travel%20roughly%20100%2C000%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20Howe%20told%20BI%20over%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%2210224%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mars%20human%20exploration%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d5b26b821214c3e4a0d618b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225144%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20PPR%20rocket%20would%20have%20to%20slow%20down%20significantly%20to%20enter%20orbit%20around%20Mars%20and%20eventually%20land.%3Cp%3EJPL%20%2F%20NASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spacecraft%20flying%20that%20fast%20would%20eventually%20have%20to%20slow%20down%20to%20reach%20its%20destination.%20Howe%20said%20the%20company%20has%20accounted%20for%20the%20additional%20energy%20and%20propellant%20this%20would%20require%20to%20land%20on%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20phase%20two%20is%20complete%2C%20it%20will%20still%20be%20about%20a%20couple%20of%20decades%20before%20the%20PPR%20is%20ready%20to%20blast%20astronauts%20off%20to%20the%20red%20planet.%20But%20once%20it's%20available%20for%20spaceflight%2C%20Howe%20hopes%20that%20this%20technology%20will%20significantly%20expand%20the%20range%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-artemis-accords-deep-space-exploration-moon-mars-asteroids-comets-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20space%20exploration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20perhaps%20even%20aiding%20missions%20to%20Pluto%20one%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20pretty%20much%20achieve%20anything%20you%20want%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-solar-system-mozart-einstein-37-000-serial-killers-2023-12%5C%2