Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-a-529-plan%5C%22%3Ecollege%20savings%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20shortly%20after%20I%20was%20born%2C%20which%20paid%20for%20my%20first%20university%20degree.%20Completing%20my%20undergraduate%20degree%20with%20very%20little%20debt%20to%20my%20name%20meant%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20master's%20degree%20on%20my%20own.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20imagine%20my%20surprise%20when%20I%20started%20a%20new%20job%20at%20a%20national%20literacy%20organization%20and%20found%20that%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2030%2C%20I%20actually%20knew%20very%20little%20about%20money%20management.%20For%20something%20so%20vital%20to%20our%20success%20in%20this%20world%2C%20it's%20a%20wonder%20that%20money%20management%20remains%20shrouded%20in%20mystery%20for%20so%20many%20of%20us.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnecting%20directly%20with%20workshop%20facilitators%20and%20teachers%20who%20delivered%20our%20financial%20literacy%20program%20to%20their%20learners%20from%20all%20walks%20of%20life%20and%20then%20managing%20a%20portfolio%20of%20literacy%20programs%2C%20it%20was%20my%20job%20to%20know%20the%20ins%20and%20outs%20of%20our%20programs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20my%20work%20was%20around%20raising%20awareness%20of%20the%20need%20for%20financial%20literacy%20and%20advocating%20for%20lifelong%20learning.%20I%20quickly%20adopted%20the%20perspective%20that%20literacy%20exists%20across%20a%20spectrum%20%E2%80%94%20you%20may%20be%20highly%20literate%20in%20some%20areas%20of%20your%20life%20and%20weaker%20in%20others.%20Through%20my%20work%20at%20this%20organization%2C%20I%20came%20to%20terms%20with%20my%20lack%20of%20financial%20literacy%20and%20took%20steps%20toward%20improving%20my%20money%20management%20skills.%20I%20learned%20three%20key%20lessons%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Money%20is%20an%20emotional%20and%20taboo%20subject%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20certain%20things%20in%20life%2C%20often%20very%20important%20things%2C%20that%20most%20of%20us%20aren't%20taught%20in%20school.%20We%20pick%20them%20up%20along%20the%20way%20through%20trial%20and%20error.%20Effective%20money%20management%20is%20one%20of%20those%20things.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20schools%20have%20mandatory%20courses%20in%20other%20life%20skills%2C%20like%20home%20economics%20or%20civics%2C%20few%20have%20financial%20literacy%20in%20the%20curriculum.%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20bake%20a%20pie%2C%20make%20a%20pillow%20in%20Family%20Studies%2C%20and%20build%20a%20bookshelf%20in%20Design%20Technology%2C%20but%20nearly%20all%20of%20my%20money%20lessons%20were%20learned%20the%20hard%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20shame%20attached%20to%20not%20knowing%20something%20that%20everyone's%20supposed%20to%20know.%20Most%20of%20us%20don't%20learn%20how%20to%20manage%20our%20money%20in%20school%2C%20and%20we%20end%20up%20ashamed%20to%20ask%20for%20help.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20with%20adult%20learners%20and%20their%20teachers%2C%20I%20heard%20variations%20of%20the%20same%20story%20again%20and%20again%20%E2%80%94%20they%20didn't%20learn%20this%20stuff%20in%20school%2C%20and%20they're%20embarrassed%20to%20admit%20it.%20The%20financial%20jargon%2C%20lack%20of%20clear%20communication%20around%20financial%20services%2C%20how%20they%20work%2C%20and%20the%20bad%20behaviors%20that%20can%20result%20from%20misconceptions%20about%20things%20like%20credit%2C%20for%20example%2C%20have%20led%20many%20nonprofits%20to%20create%20educational%20content%20to%20help%20people%20improve%20their%20financial%20literacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20lots%20of%20free%20programs%20out%20there%20that%20focus%20on%20areas%20like%20debt%20reduction%2C%20building%20your%20savings%2C%20knowing%20your%20money%20rights%2C%20and%20banking%20basics.%20If%20you're%20looking%20to%20increase%20your%20financial%20literacy%2C%20whatever%20your%20existing%20knowledge%2C%20start%20by%20connecting%20with%20your%20bank%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20the%20larger%20banks%20sponsor%20nonprofits%20to%20create%20and%20share%20programs%20and%20materials%20to%20help%20you%20do%20just%20that.%20You%20can%20also%20look%20into%20government-sponsored%20and%20recommended%20programs%20to%20help%20you%20up%20your%20skills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20There's%20good%20debt%20and%20there's%20bad%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20feel%20very%20different%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20it's%20true%3A%20There's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fgood-debt-vs-bad-debt%5C%22%3Egood%20debt%20and%20bad%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20North%20America%2C%20our%20banking%20and%20financial%20structures%20are%20set%20up%20to%20rely%20on%20credit.%20We%20need%20credit%20to%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20rent%20an%20apartment%2C%20lease%20a%20car%2C%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20to%20get%20a%20job.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-a-good-credit-score%5C%22%3Egood%20credit%20score%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20that%20you%20have%20a%20history%20of%20paying%20your%20debt%20on%20time.%20Bad%20credit%20means%20you%20don't.%20But%20in%20order%20to%20build%20credit%2C%20you%20need%20a%20credit%20card%20or%20a%20loan%20%E2%80%94%20something%20to%20prove%20that%20you%20can%20manage%20your%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20adults%20think%20that%20all%20debt%20is%20bad%20debt.%20But%20what%20about%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F30-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3Emortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20How%20many%20people%20do%20you%20know%20who%20bought%20their%20first%20home%20in%20cash%3F%20A%20mortgage%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20within%20your%20means%2C%20is%20generally%20considered%20good%20debt.%20It's%20the%20kind%20of%20debt%20that%20you%20pay%20off%20slowly%20and%20steadily%2C%20adding%20to%20your%20good%20credit%20and%20showing%20creditors%20that%20you're%20a%20safe%20bet.%20Having%20a%20good%20credit%20score%20means%20that%20more%20doors%20are%20open%20to%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20bought%20my%20first%20home%20just%20over%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20moving%20from%20a%20big%20city%20to%20a%20small%20town.%20My%20mortgage%20is%20a%20little%20over%20half%20what%20my%20rent%20was%20for%20my%20humble%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20the%20city.%20When%20I%20bought%20the%20place%2C%20I'd%20been%20debt-free%20for%20nearly%2010%20years%2C%20so%20it%20took%20me%20a%20while%20to%20come%20around%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20taking%20on%20debt%20was%20a%20good%20idea.%20My%20exposure%20to%20financial%20literacy%20education%20helped%20me%20make%20the%20mental%20and%20emotional%20journey%20toward%20homeownership%20by%20adjusting%20my%20views%20of%20debt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20bad%20debt.%20That's%20the%20debt%20we%20rack%20up%20on%20credit%20cards%20while%20living%20beyond%20our%20means.%20Using%20your%20credit%20card%20to%20pay%20your%20bills%2C%20pay%20for%20groceries%20etc.%2C%20is%20good%20debt%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you%20pay%20it%20all%20down%20to%20zero%20at%20the%20end%20of%20every%20month.%20I%20realize%20that%20this%20sounds%20pretty%20straightforward.%20I'm%20more%20than%20a%20little%20embarrassed%20to%20tell%20you%20that%20it%20was%20news%20to%20me%20when%20I%20first%20started%20working%20in%20financial%20literacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20'Paying%20yourself%20first'%20is%20a%20pain-free%20way%20to%20save%20and%20invest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20simple%20yet%20effective%20money-management%20principle%20I%20learned%20was%20to%20pay%20myself%20first.%20Following%20the%20psychology%20of%20money%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthedecisionlab.com%2Freference-guide%2Fpsychology%2Fpain-of-paying%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaying%20is%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Every%20time%20we%20pay%20for%20something%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.behavioraleconomics.com%2Fresources%2Fmini-encyclopedia-of-be%2Fpain-of-paying%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epain%20center%20of%20our%20brain%20is%20activated%3C%2Fa%3E.%20No%2C%20really.%20So%2C%20as%20a%20way%20to%20bypass%20this%20response%2C%20one%20of%20the%20best%20and%20least%20painful%20ways%20to%20save%20and%20invest%20is%20to%20set%20up%20auto-deposits%20from%20your%20bank%20account%20each%20month%20in%20a%20dollar%20amount%20that%20still%20allows%20you%20to%20cover%20your%20basic%20needs.%20If%20the%20money%20comes%20straight%20out%20of%20your%20account%20each%20month%2C%20it's%20like%20it%20never%20existed%2C%20like%20it%20was%20never%20really%20available%20to%20spend.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20new%20change%20to%20my%20income%2C%20I%20adjust%20my%20monthly%20auto-deposit%20amounts%2C%20one%20to%20my%20home%20renovations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3Esavings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20other%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20I%20left%20my%20permanent%2C%20salaried%2C%20nonprofit%20job%20last%20summer%20to%20go%20freelance%2C%20I%20reduced%20the%20monthly%20amounts%20and%20have%20been%20gradually%20increasing%20and%20adjusting%20them%20as%20I%20get%20a%20better%20sense%20of%20my%20average%20earnings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoney%20is%20inherently%20emotional.%20And%20it's%20a%20taboo%20subject%20in%20most%20Western%20cultures%2C%20so%20the%20odds%20really%20are%20stacked%20against%20us%20if%20we%20don't%20start%20teaching%20financial%20literacy%20in%20schools%20and%20getting%20comfortable%20talking%20about%20something%20so%20important.%20As%20a%20writer%20and%20educator%2C%20I%20continue%20to%20work%20in%20and%20advocate%20for%20literacy.%20Helping%20adult%20learners%20increase%20their%20financial%20literacy%20ha