20outage%20is.%20We%20only%20come%20to%20know%20about%20a%20power%20shutdown%20when%20we%20hear%20the%20noise%20of%20a%20generator%20from%20the%20nearby%20hotel%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20couple%20has%20brought%20down%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F312672%2Fpuducherry-dr-brahmanand-mohanty-builds-fully-solar-powered-home-pays-zero-electricity-bill%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epower%20bills%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%2090%20percent.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20power%20bills%20for%20our%20neighbours%20in%20a%20similar%20set%20up%20of%20the%20bungalow%20is%20between%20Rs%206%2C000%20and%20Rs%2010%2C000%20per%20month.%20Whereas%2C%20we%20get%20bills%20between%20Rs%20700%20and%20Rs%201%2C500.%20Of%20which%2C%20about%20Rs%20500%20is%20the%20fixed%20component%20for%20having%20a%20metered%20connection.%20Simply%20put%2C%20we%20get%20a%20nominal%20power%20bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Suneet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-3-1720704177.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%202020%2C%20when%20the%20couple%20moved%20to%20their%20bungalow%20in%20Goodwill%20community%2C%20the%20obvious%20choice%20was%20to%20install%20solar%20panels.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-3-1720704177.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-3-1720704177-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-3-1720704177-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-3-1720704177-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-3-1720704177-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-356553%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIn%202020%2C%20when%20the%20couple%20moved%20to%20their%20bungalow%20in%20Goodwill%20community%2C%20the%20obvious%20choice%20was%20to%20install%20solar%20panels.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIntrigued%20by%20their%20way%20of%20life%2C%20we%20sat%20down%20with%20the%20couple%20to%20know%20how%20they%20achieved%20energy%20self-sufficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENet-metered%20vs%20grid-backed%20power%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShilpa%20and%20Suneet%2C%20both%20polymer%20engineers%2C%20run%20a%20solar%20PV%20installation%20company.%20In%202020%2C%20when%20the%20couple%20moved%20to%20their%20bungalow%20in%20Goodwill%20community%2C%20the%20obvious%20choice%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F352016%2Fhow-to-harvest-solar-energy-panels-in-apartments-homes-rentals-guide-to-save-electricity-bills%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einstall%20solar%20panels%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20house%20was%20constructed%20in%201984.%20After%20we%20became%20parents%2C%20we%20moved%20into%20one%20of%20the%20newer%20modern%20complexes%20where%20the%20kids%20could%20have%20more%20friend%20circles%2C%20better%20schools%20and%20amenities.%20Now%20that%20they%20are%20grown%20up%2C%20we%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20house%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shilpa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%20Suneet%2C%20who%20was%20always%20interested%20in%20reducing%20their%20energy%20footprint%20and%20adopting%20sustainable%20manners%20of%20living%2C%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20wife%20encouraged%20me%20to%20be%20enthused%20and%20come%20up%20with%20solutions%20where%20we%20did%20not%20compromise%20on%20our%20quality%20and%20standard%20of%20living.%20Otherwise%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20very%20easy%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20this%20and%20be%20sustainable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20decided%20to%20go%20off-grid.%20%E2%80%9CNormally%2C%20people%20believe%20that%20large%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2Fweb-stories%2Fsolar-powered-homes-of-india-rooftop-panels-save-electricity-bills%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar%20PV%20installations%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecan%20only%20be%20done%20for%20farmhouses.%20We%20wanted%20to%20prove%20that%20we%20can%20lead%20sustainable%20lives%20even%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20bustling%20city%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shilpa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20moving%20to%20the%20bungalow%2C%20the%20couple%20installed%2042%20panels%20of%202%C3%971%20metres%20each%2C%20spread%20across%2021%20sq%20m%20of%20the%20terrace.%20While%20the%20installation%20took%20two%20weeks%2C%20building%20the%20whole%20electronics%20took%20them%20about%20eight%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22For%20Shilpa%20and%20Suneet%2C%20the%20first%20biggest%20transformation%20with%20this%20setup%20was%20to%20have%20an%20uninterrupted%20power%20supply.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-356495%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFor%20Shilpa%20and%20Suneet%2C%20the%20first%20biggest%20transformation%20with%20this%20setup%20was%20to%20have%20an%20uninterrupted%20power%20supply.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20grid-backed%20setfup%20was%20different%20from%20a%20net-metered%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20two%2C%20Suneet%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20net-metered%20system%2C%20you%20do%20not%20require%20to%20store%20the%20energy%20and%20feed%20excess%20energy%20to%20the%20grid%20and%20get%20it%20back%20from%20it%20when%20you%20are%20not%20generating%20enough%20power.%20It%20is%20a%20more%20economical%20way%20for%20harnessing%20solar%20energy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20grid-backed%20setup%2C%20we%20do%20not%20feed%20excess%20power%20to%20the%20grid%2C%20we%20instead%20store%20the%20excess%20energy%20and%20use%20it%20during%20non-generation%20hours%2C%20say%20during%20the%20nights%20and%20cloudy%20days.%20We%20have%20our%20own%20backup.%20As%20long%20as%20I%20am%20dependent%20on%20the%20grid%2C%20we%20are%20responsible%20for%20coal-backed%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20major%20production%20of%20electricity%20is%20achieved%20through%20coal%20thermal%20power%20plants%20which%20is%20around%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coal.nic.in%2Fen%2Fmajor-statistics%2Fgeneration-of-thermal-power-from-raw-coal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%20percent%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20total%20power%20generation.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20want%20to%20reduce%20your%20carbon%20footprint%2C%20you%20need%20to%20reduce%20your%20dependence%20on%20coal%20and%20thermal%20energy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBesides%2C%20if%20the%20grid%20in%20the%20net-metre%20system%20decides%20to%20shut%20down%2C%20my%20house%20will%20still%20be%20in%20darkness%20even%20though%20I%20am%20generating%20power%20from%20solar%20energy.%20The%20grid-backed%20system%20helps%20us%20create%20power%20backup%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESelf-dependent%20on%20energy%20%26amp%3B%20water%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20couple%20has%20not%20given%20up%20on%20their%20electricity%20metre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20couple%20planned%20a%20grid%20backed%20solar%20photovoltaic%20(PV)%20system%20in%20the%20house%20with%20a%2015%20kWp%20capacity.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-356501%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20couple%20planned%20a%20grid%20backed%20solar%20photovoltaic%20(PV)%20system%20in%20the%20house%20with%20a%2015%20kWp%20capacity.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20only%20I%20was%20convinced%20about%20this%20setup%2C%20so%20we%20had%20to%20keep%20the%20grid%20as%20a%20backup.%20We%20have%20programmed%20the%20system%20in%20such%20a%20way%